---
title: Chicken Sausage, Garlic & Mushroom Flatbreads with White Sauce, Mozzarella & Grape Tomatoes
description: Move over, marinara—there’s a new sauce in town. In this recipe, crispy flatbreads are slathered with a rich, creamy white sauce we just can’t get enough of. We top it off with melty mozzarella and roasted garlic, plus tender mushrooms and juicy marinated tomatoes. Sprinkle with chives and chili flakes if you like a little zip, then sit back and enjoy.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64a5ae9e47daed9d1c1176c7-0303ca83.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64a5ae9e47daed9d1c1176c7.pdf
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 880 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 2080 mg
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-sausage-garlic-and-mushroom-flatbreads-64a5ae9e47daed9d1c1176c7
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} into ½-inch-thick pieces. Peel @garlic{1%clove} and place in the center of a small piece of #foil{}; drizzle with @olive oil{1%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cinch into a packet. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Mince @chives{1/4%ounce}.

Place garlic foil packet on a #baking sheet{}. Roast on top rack for ~{15%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

While garlic roasts, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and @italian seasoning{1%tsp}; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, place tomatoes in a #medium bowl{}; toss with @italian seasoning{1%tsp}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. (You'll use the rest of the Italian Seasoning later.) Set aside to marinate.

Cut chicken into bite-size pieces if necessary. Pat dry with paper towels and season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add @italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Wipe out pan.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Transfer cooked mushrooms to bowl with tomatoes; toss to combine.

Leaving garlic foil packet on baking sheet, place @flatbreads{2} on same sheet. Return to top rack until flatbreads are lightly toasted and garlic is softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

While flatbreads toast, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add @flour{1%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and remaining @italian seasoning{1%tsp}. Cook, whisking constantly, until lightly browned, ~{30%seconds}.

Reduce heat to medium low and whisk in @cream cheese{4%tbsp} and @water{1/2%cup} until melted and combined. Season generously with salt and pepper. Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Once roasted garlic is done, carefully transfer to a #cutting board{} and roughly chop.

Heat broiler to high.

Evenly top flatbreads with sauce, roasted garlic, and veggies. Sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Top flatbreads with chicken or sausage along with veggies.

Broil flatbreads until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}. Slice flatbreads into pieces; sprinkle with chives and @?chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste. Divide between plates and serve.

> Sprinkle with chives and chili flakes if you like a little zip, then sit back and enjoy.